original: Lindsten, Tyrgils Sten Axel Bernhard, komminister, Barnarp, Jönköping, f. 7/1/07 i Värnamo av Sven L. o. Emilia Johansson. G. 37 m. Lin-néa Norén. Barn: Dag f. 44. — Stud:-ex. v. Fjellstedtska skolan i Upps. 31, teol. fil. ex. i Lund 32, teol. kand. 34, prakt. teol. prov i Upps. samt prästv. f. Växjö stift 35. Tjg. som pastiadj. i Berga, v. kommin. i Almesåkra samt v. pastor i Göteryd 36-41, vakanskom-min. i Månsarp 41, kommin. i Barnarp sed. 43.
translated: Lindsten, Tyrgils Sten Axel Bernhard, assistant pastor, Barnarp, Jönköping, born on January 7th, 1907 in Värnamo, to Sven L. and Emilia Johansson. Married in 1937 to Linnea Norén. Children: Dag, born in 1944. Completed secondary school at Fjellstedtska school in Uppsala in 1931, obtained a degree in theology from Lund in 1932, completed theological studies in 1934, practical theological examination in Uppsala, and ordained as a priest for Växjö diocese in 1935. Served as a curate in Berga, assistant pastor in Almesåkra, and pastor in Göteryd from 1936 to 1941, temporary pastor in Månsarp in 1941, and as a pastor in Barnarp since 1943.
